    "long_instructions": "### Always Been You\r\n\r\nYou've been given just the vocals for the chorus of this song. Your job is to come up with the backing tracks for beats, bass, and lead. To design your remix, you'll need to use **decomposition** to break the problem into smaller parts and build up each one individually.\r\n\r\n**Your task:** Use decomposition to separate the remix into three parts: beat, bass, and lead. For each one, define a function using tracks that complement the vocals. Then bring the parts together by calling all the functions in your code. Feel free to mix genres or use the original tracks!\r\n\r\nWhen you're finished, your code should look similar to this:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/6eba847b3ad2ef5f4b5aaed4a25fc61f-image-1742271279390.png)",
    "display_name": "Always Been You",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Use functions to add backing beats, bass, and lead tracks to the chorus of this song.",
